    "name": "Notzing (2)",
    "profile": "Notzing is an ongoing exploration of altered perception through sound. Dense drones, structural minimalism, and time-stretched loops converge to dissolve linearity and summon trance.\r\nInfluenced by oneiricism and surrealism, Notzing navigates the unconscious through sonic language — sculpting frequencies, bending time, displacing space. Modular synthesis, feedback chains, and processed textures act not as instruments but as conduits for dreamlike experience.\r\nIt is a ritual practice in cycles: sonic, thematic, subconscious. There is no final form — only recurrences, echoes, and the slow drift toward the unreal.",
